	<div itemprop="text"><p>The last 2 functions you describe:</p>
<pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate" title="">
function plugin_setting_string() {
        $options = get_option('plugin_options');
        echo &quot;&lt;input id='plugin_text_string' name='plugin_options[text_string]' size='40' type='text' value='{$options['text_string']}' /&gt;&quot;;
    }
</pre>
<p>And: </p>
<pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate" title="">

    // validate our options
    function plugin_options_validate($input) {
        $newinput['text_string'] = trim($input['text_string']);
        if(!preg_match('/^[a-z0-9]{32}$/i', $newinput['text_string'])) {
            $newinput['text_string'] = '';
        }
        return $newinput;
    }
</pre>
<p>Should these be inside the function:
<pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate" title="">function plugin_admin_init(){</pre>
<p> ?</p>
<p>Could you perhaps add source file&#8217;s so I can download them and compare them.</p>
