	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2009/wordpress-settings-api-tutorial/comment-page-2/#comment-12106">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2013-10-29T16:29:44+00:00">October 29, 2013 at 4:29 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Tutorial has: register_setting( &#8216;plugin_options&#8217;, &#8216;plugin_options&#8217;, &#8216;plugin_options_validate&#8217; );</p>
<p>First is Group ID.</p>
<p>Tutorial has: settings_fields(&#8216;plugin_options&#8217;);</p>
<p>WP Codex says settings_fields is looking for Group ID not Name.</p>
<p>Should be settings_fields(&#8216;plugin-options&#8217;);</p>
<p>Not that it works this way for me either. =)</p>
<p>Now the page just reloads without saving (Yes i have entered in valid data).</p>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
	<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2009/wordpress-settings-api-tutorial/comment-page-2/?replytocom=12106#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-12106", "12106", "respond", "39")'>Reply to this comment</a>	</div>
		</div>
